			<p>
				üóùÔ∏è <m>\textbf{Key Takeaways...}</m>
				<ul marker="square">
					<li><em>Uncoupled systems</em> have no interaction between equations: each variable evolves independently.</li>
					<li>You solve each equation on its own, then pair the solutions as <m>(x(t), y(t))</m>.</li>
					<li>These are the simplest systems ‚Äî but they're still systems!</li>
				</ul>
			</p>
		</assemblage>
